Vice President Mike Pence chaired the first meeting of the National Space Council in 25 years at the National Air and Space Museum in Virginia. The conference, titled "Leading the Next Frontier: An Event with the National Space Council," brought together members from various sectors of the space community to discuss the future of space exploration. The Vice President emphasized the importance of reviving the United States' efforts in the space race and creating a partnership between the federal government and the space industry. The council will coordinate all national space activities, from security to commerce to exploration. The Vice President concluded by stating that the United States will usher in a new era of space leadership under President Trump's guidance and with the National Space Council's support. The National Space Council was revived by an Executive Order signed by President Trump on June 30, 2017.